args:
The imperial army pursues the party to a town
where they are saved by Annelie, the ringmaster
of a circus troupe, and her dagger expert, Fritz.
As thanks for sheltering them, the party invites
the entire circus troupe to the Halidom.
The prince and his friends have arrived at\na town near the Halidom.
There, they are greeted by a massive\nred-and-white big top.
That is one large tent right there.\nYou think it might be a circus?
So it would seem. Is this your first time\nseeing one, Your Highness?
Yes. I've heard and read about them,\nbut I've never been to one in person.
Well, since we're here, perhaps it wouldn't\ngo amiss to let off a little steam...
What the hell's the imperial army\ndoin' here?!
If we fight them here, civilians will be\ncaught in the crossfire. Everyone run!
*pant* *pant* Ugh, those jerks are a\npersistent bunch!
There's too many of them; we're going\nto be surrounded at this rate.
Hey! Someone just showed up and\ndragged {player_name} away!
Your Highness! Are you all right?!
Be quiet, or the soldiers will hear you!
Are you the one who brought me here?
If you stay here, they won't find you,\nso just hang tight for a while.
Welcome, one and all, to the fascinating,\nfantastical, and fabulous world of...\nthe ciiiircuuuus!
Sounds like the show is starting.

Our troupe, lead by our illustrious
ringmaster Annelie, is about to take
you on a fantastic journey to the world
of magic and dreams!
But first, I—Fritz the Magnificent—will\ndazzle you with my splendiferous\ndagger-throwing skills!
Gaze now at yonder moving targets,\nand watch in amazement as I pierce\neach and every one clean through!
Goodness! That young man has some\nimpressive skills.
And now, please welcome to the stage\nour ringmaster, the Sugary Star herself,\nAaaaaannelieeeeeee!
Hey, it's the girl from earlier!\nI guess she's the ringmaster.
Hold a moment. Is that a wild animal\nI see behind her?
This ferocious dragon will now perform,\nperfectly in sync with the lovely Annelie!\nHold onto your hats as they—
They're going to ruin the show!
Oh ho! What do we have here, ladies\nand gentlemen? Some unexpected guests?\nWell, all are welcome under THIS tent!
Come, Liger! Give me a ride so we can\ngreet our new friends!
Welcome to the show, my imperial friends!\nI DO hope you enjoy it!
Oh, and here—a souvenir bundle of\nballoons, just for you!
Oh hey, thank—HEY! We're not here\nfor a bunch of balloons!

But this is the circus; a place for each and
every soul to forget the real world and
enjoy a few moments in the grasp of
the fun and fantastical!

Now, feast your eyes! Gaze in breathtaking
wonderment at the dragon's performance,
the trapeze artists, and the death-defying
tightrope walkers!
And in this world of illusions, my friends,\nI will be your guide!
Hey! Quit pushing me already!\nWe're sitting, we're sitting!\nJust for a second though.
Thank you so much for joining us today,\nand do come again soon!
Oh man! I thought the circus would be\na waste of time, but that was one heck\nof a show we just saw!
Anyway, looks like the prince isn't here,\nso let's get going.

Sorry to keep you waiting, friends.
Also, you seem to have some VERY
angry people with a keen interest in
learning your current whereabouts!
Yes, and we're sorry about that.\nThank you for hiding us.
I'm sorry those men ended up interrupting\nyour performance.
Aw, don't worry about it. After all,\nthe show must go on!
When you're in this line of work,\nyou get used to a little improvisation.
Plus, saving you was a fun little way\nto get back at them!
Thanks to the devastation they've wrought,\nwe're quickly running out of towns to visit.
Hence, getting back at them! *wink*\nAh, but that DID feel good.
Oh, wait! We haven't done proper intros!\nI'm Annelie, the ringmaster of this troupe.
I'm also a world-class dragon tamer.
Yeah, I saw you working with that dragon\nearlier and could hardly believe my eyes.
I never thought I'd see a dragon perform\nin front of a crowd!
I, too, have never seen the like.
Aw, aren't you guys just the sweetest?\nOh, hey! This is Liger, by the way.\nSay hello, Liger!
And I'm Fritz, the dagger man.\nNice to meetcha.
Is there anything we can do to repay you\nfor all that you've done?
Like I said, think nothing of it.\nHelping you out helped us as well!
But we would have been in real trouble\nif you hadn't been around.
So if you can think of a way we might\nrepay you, please just let me know.
Weeell...I suppose we DO need a place\nto put on our next performance.
See, there's a town beyond the mountains\nwhere they hold an annual circus festival.
Troupes from all over meet up there and\ncompete to see who has the greatest\ncircus showmanship.
That sounds interesting. Er, but what does\nit have to do with finding a location for\nyour next performance?
'Cause we need more manpower if\nwe want to—

Publicity! Yes, that's it. We want to get
gums flapping about us before we visit
the big festival, and another performance
is just the thing.
Yeah, it's a pretty crazy request, I know.\nDon't worry your head too much about it.
Well, you could put on a show at the\nHalidom if you wanted.
I'd love for everyone who lives there to\nget a chance to see your work.
What a wonderful idea! We could all use\na break from our workaday cares.
Then it's settled! We'll throw up that tent\ninside the castle and give everybody a\nmorale boost they won't forget!
That sounds like a great idea!
Be a shame to turn down a goodwill\ngesture like this, eh, ma'am?
Right you are, Fritz! We gladly accept.\nFrankly, I'm surprised we got this\nsorted out so quickly.
Then let's head back to the castle and\nget this show on the road!
